New illo from me -_-;;<br>
<br>
The idea for this pic sat around in my head for several days before I finally drew it. I play JK2 (Jedi Knight II) more often than is healthy... and I always use this imperial/officer model to duel with. I imagined this character sort of like Saito from Kenshin...<br>
<br>
Thus you have here an Imperial officer with a lightsaber in Saito's sword style (slightly off... and modified).<br>
<br>
Now before you even begin critting, yes I do know the arms and legs are super duper long and yes I know this pose is painful and yes the angle of view tweaks everything to hell. Partly the fault of not having drawn other poses and partly the fault of not having drawn at all for very long periods of time. I still want you to critique that though. Give it your best shot. <br>
<br>
Otherwise, please comment on the style of the drawing, specifically the way I used pencil shading. I don't do this often so I wonder how well this worked in concert with the CG.<br>
<br>
For those of you eager colorists here is the lineart... in reduced form:<br>
http://xenoflare.virtualave.net/misc/jediColorMe.jpg
